 Two women, Gina Otto and Moeka Gravina, were attacked shortly after arriving at Mrs Otto’s house. The women were tortured for hours before they were loaded into Mrs Otto’s car and dumped next to the road, underway to Lydenburg. Mrs Otto was found by a passing truck driver on Friday night whilst police found Mrs Gravina next to the road the following morning. Both women were injured and required medical attention. Ms. Moeka Gravina(70) and her friend were brutally tortured in the Roossenekal farm attack. Their two attackers proceeded to Lydenburg where they picked up two sex workers in Mrs Otto’s car. Police attempted to pull them over, resulting in a shootout.
One man, Petros Mpho Sithole (32), was fatally wounded in the shootout. Also read: Farm attack: ‘How sick are these men?’ The second suspect fled on foot and has been on the run since then. •Anyone with information about Mr Mthimunye’s whereabouts can contact Sakkie Louwrens from the Heritage Protection Group on 071 798 7954.  R10 000 reward for information ‘We should kill him’ – Truck driver hears how hijackers argue about his fate #TrafficUpdate: Avoid N4 near Machadodorp VIDEO: Machadodorp two granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za